The article discusses the flaws in the US immigration system, particularly the visa lottery and chain migration. It argues that these programs do not benefit America and its citizens, and instead allow foreigners with bad intentions to enter the country. The article mentions the recent terrorist attack in New York City, where the alleged perpetrator entered the US through the visa lottery. It also highlights the RAISE Act, a proposed legislation that aims to end the visa lottery program and prioritize merit-based immigration. The article concludes by urging lawmakers to take action to protect American citizens.